==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Æolotropic
<hw>⟦AE⟧`o*lo*trop"ic</hw></mhw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ changeful + <?/ a turning,
<?/ to turn.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>Exhibiting differences of
quality or property in different directions; having properties with
different values along different axes; not isotropic. In specialized
contexts, synonymous with <stype>anisotropic</stype>.</def> <altsp>[Also
spelled <asp>eolotropic</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Sir W.
Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> </syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>AEolotropy</ent>⟦br⟧
